Question 2 
Part A = sundays' helper function starts recursion of calculating if first of the month is Sunday, if it is  it wait the result of the recursion that started by calculated nextY and nextM values and increases the number of Sundays by 1 (result of the recursion below it).

Part B =  If we only use the expression instead of defining the readability will be worse.

Question 5

In gregorian calendar there is 400-year cycle of leap years so every 400 years will have the same number of weeks. Therefore all days are equally possible for being  a sunday since 400 years is an integer which can be divided by 7 without reminder.